Africa’s Global Bank, the United Bank for Africa Plc, has rewarded its loyal customers in its UBA Super Savers draw with N16.6m cash prizes. The computerised draw held at the UBA Head Office on Friday, and was witnessed by representatives of the National Lottery Regulatory Commission and the Consumer Protection Council. A breakdown of the prizes comprised 12 new millionaires who won a total of N13.2m; one person got N500,000; 20 Bumper account holders won N100,000 each totalling N2m; 10 Savings Account customers won N1m totalling N10m; and five NextGen customers won N15,000 per person every month for a year, totalling N900,000. For the Bumper account draw, Elisha Yusuf, a UBA Bumper account holder, emerged winner of the N2m prize; Naomi Ogoma Aba, another customer of the bank won N1.2m; while Veronica Logbo, was rewarded with N500,000 at the draws. The Head, Personal Banking, UBA, Ogechi Altraide, who congratulated all the winners after the draw, said the bank is putting smiles on the faces of its customers and encouraging them to cultivate the culture of savings. She said, “At UBA, we are all about encouraging our customers to imbibe the savings culture, to be able to achieve their dreams, while putting away something for the future. This time around, we have given away huge prizes as can be seen today; with the aim of appreciating our customers who believe in us and have trusted the bank with their funds.” Altraide encouraged customers who did not win during the promo to prepare for the next draws which would be announced soon.  Contact: theeditor@punchng.com Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com